It's time to give the bedroom a thorough makeover. This is the last room in the house that has only been simply decorated.
Remove the ugly electric wall heater and fireplace. Seal the chimney, replace the cracked mortar, and repaint. Customize a closet.
We usually start by drawing a rough pencil sketch…
The messy stage is over.
We found several dead birds behind the chimney, their bodies completely dried out :(
Prepare to welcome the trowel workers next week
I'm satisfied with the small niche next to it
We'll put the new closet here (we haven't even started designing it yet 🙈)
Ha ha, look what we found behind the heating unit!
Do you remember adding the cute ventilation holes to prevent the chimney from getting damp?
The chimney cap and chimney crown have been installed. The white-billed magpies that like to nest in the chimney should be safer now.
The plastering work is complete. We'll lay the floor tomorrow!
The soft foam mats have been laid, and we've made a dusting attachment for the vacuum cleaner using a roll of toilet paper to pick up sawdust.
Some of the floorboards have been prepared, and we can start laying them. Let's take a break and have a cup of tea first.
Yes, today's progress was a bit slow because we had to cut around the doorframe to ensure a seamless connection with the corridor (which is also being floored), and it was a bit of a hassle. @user45@twitter.com has been complaining about me.
Finally, it's completed, but it's a mess! What's even worse is that the assembly instructions for the new bed are terrible. I can finally get a good night's sleep tonight!
The corridor floor and baseboard are still not done. The contractor only came a month ago, so we're just having to make do for now, and the room is just bare plasterboard.
Last night, I did a quick DIY and used a coping saw and chisel to cut out a part of the doorframe, so the floor can be laid perfectly underneath.
The softwood underlayment for the corridor is also laid.
We finished laying the corridor floor yesterday! This morning, I got up at 5 am to go to Heathrow Airport to pick up package 1, and then I took a nap, and now I can finally start laying the baseboard for the corridor. We'll fill in the gaps once the glue is dry.
